olive oil
1 packet button mushrooms
1 packet lamb mince
1 bag Soffritto Mix
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet tomato paste
1 packet fusilli
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
2.25 cup boiling water
1 packet Worcestershire sauce
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Thinly slice button mushrooms. Boil the kettle.
• In a large deep frying (or saucepan), heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook mushrooms until browned and softened, 8-10 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook lamb mince and soffritto mix, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 5-7 minutes.
• Add garlic & herb seasoning and tomato paste and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.

• Add penne, vegetable stock powder, mushrooms, the boiling water (21/4 cups for 2 people / 41/2 cups for 4 people) and a pinch of salt.
• Bring to the boil, then reduce heat to medium-low and cover with a lid. Cook, stirring occasionally, until pasta is 'al dente', 12-15 minutes.
• Add Worcestershire sauce and stir to combine.

• Divide one-pan garlic and lamb penne between bowls.
• Top with grated Parmesan cheese to serve. Enjoy!